@tsapi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5234

# BorrowLend API - HTTP Requests
# 
# NOTE: Item image uploads use multipart/form-data and require special tooling.
# For image upload testing, use Swagger UI (https://localhost:7117/) which provides
# a user-friendly file upload interface.
# 
# FEATURES:
# - Item image uploads (JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP, max 5MB)
# - Search and filtering (case-insensitive)
# - Pagination on all list endpoints (default: 10/page, max: 100)
# - Direct image URLs in responses (e.g., https://localhost:7117/images/items/abc.jpg)

### Register User 1
POST {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "firstName": "Alice",
  "lastName": "Smith"
}

### Register User 2
POST {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "firstName": "Bob",
  "lastName": "Johnson"
}

### Get All Users
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/users

### Get User by Email
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/users/email/alice@example.com

### Create Item WITHOUT Image
# Note: Item creation now expects multipart/form-data for image support.
# This simple JSON request won't work anymore. Use Swagger UI for creating items with/without images.
# Or use a tool that supports multipart/form-data (curl, Postman, etc.)
# Example curl:
# curl -X POST "http://localhost:5234/api/items" \
#   -F "name=Lawn Mower" \
#   -F "description=Electric mower" \
#   -F "ownerId=user-guid"
#   -F "image=@photo.jpg"

### Get All Items (with pagination - default page 1, size 10)
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/items

### Get All Items (custom pagination)
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/items?pageNumber=1&pageSize=5

### Search Items by name or description
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/items?searchQuery=mower

### Filter Items by Status
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/items?status=Available

### Combine Search, Filter, and Pagination
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/items?searchQuery=camera&status=Available&pageSize=20

### Get Available Items (with search and pagination)
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/items/available?searchQuery=bike&pageSize=15

### Get Items by Owner (replace {ownerId}, with pagination)
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/items/owned-by/{ownerId}?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10

### Borrow Item (replace {borrowerId} and itemId)
POST {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/borrowings?borrowerId={borrowerId}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "itemId": 1,
  "dueDate": "2024-12-31T00:00:00Z",
  "notes": "Need it for the weekend"
}

### Get Items Borrowed by User (replace {userId})
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/borrowings/borrowed-by/{userId}

### Get Items Lent by User (replace {userId})
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/borrowings/lent-by/{userId}

### Return Item (replace {borrowingId})
POST {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/borrowings/{borrowingId}/return
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Returned in good condition, thanks!"
}

### Mark Item as Lost (replace {borrowingId})
POST {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/borrowings/{borrowingId}/lost
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Unfortunately lost the item"
}

### Create Rating (replace {raterUserId} and ratedUserId)
POST {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/ratings?raterUserId={raterUserId}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ratedUserId": "{ratedUserId}",
  "borrowingRecordId": 1,
  "rating": 5,
  "comment": "Excellent borrower, returned on time!"
}

### Get Ratings for User (replace {userId})
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/ratings/user/{userId}

### Get User with Updated Rating (replace {userId})
GET {{tsapi_HostAddress}}/api/users/{userId}

###
